essions with rational coefficients.'), ('1301', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.EE.A.2', '2', null, null, null, 'Understand that rewriting an expression in different forms in a problem context can shed light on the problem and how the quantities in it are related.'), ('1302', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.EE.B', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve real-life and mathematical problems using numerical and algebraic expressions and equations.'), ('1303', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.EE.B.3', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve multi-step real-life and mathematical problems posed with positive and negative rational numbers in any form (whole numbers, fractions, and decimals), using tools strategically. Apply properties of operations to calculate with numbers in any form; c'), ('1304', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.EE.B.4', '2', null, null, null, 'Use variables to represent quantities in a real-world or mathematical problem, and construct simple equations and inequalities to solve problems by reasoning about the quantities.'), ('1305', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.EE.B.4a', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve word problems leading to equations of the form px + q = r and p(x + q) = r, where p, q, and r are specific rational numbers. Solve equations of these forms fluently. Compare an algebraic solution to an arithmetic solution, identifying the sequence o'), ('1306', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.EE.B.4b', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve word problems leading to inequalities of the form px + q &gt; r or px + q &lt; r, where p, q, and r are specific rational numbers. Graph the solution set of the inequality and interpret it in the context of the problem.'), ('1307', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.G.A', '2', null, null, null, 'Draw, construct, and describe geometrical figures and describe the relationships between them.'), ('1308', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.G.A.1', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve problems involving scale drawings of geometric figures, including computing actual lengths and areas from a scale drawing and reproducing a scale drawing at a different scale.'), ('1309', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.G.A.2', '2', null, null, null, 'Draw (freehand, with ruler and protractor, and with technology) geometric shapes with given conditions. Focus on constructing triangles from three measures of angles or sides, noticing when the conditions determine a unique triangle, more than one triangl'), ('1310', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.G.A.3', '2', null, null, null, 'Describe the two-dimensional figures that result from slicing three-dimensional figures, as in plane sections of right rectangular prisms and right rectangular pyramids.'), ('1311', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.G.B', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve real-life and mathematical problems involving angle measure, area, surface area, and volume.'), ('1312', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.G.B.4', '2', null, null, null, 'Know the formulas for the area and circumference of a circle and use them to solve problems; give an informal derivation of the relationship between the circumference and area of a circle.'), ('1313', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.G.B.5', '2', null, null, null, 'Use facts about supplementary, complementary, vertical, and adjacent angles in a multi-step problem to write and solve simple equations for an unknown angle in a figure.'), ('1314', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.G.B.6', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve real-world and mathematical problems involving area, volume and surface area of two- and three-dimensional objects composed of triangles, quadrilaterals, polygons, cubes, and right prisms.'), ('1315', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply and extend previous understandings of operations with fractions to add, subtract, multiply, and divide rational numbers.'), ('1316', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.1', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply and extend previous understandings of addition and subtraction to add and subtract rational numbers; represent addition and subtraction on a horizontal or vertical number line diagram.'), ('1317', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.1a', '2', null, null, null, 'Describe situations in which opposite quantities combine to make 0.'), ('1318', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.1b', '2', null, null, null, 'Understand p + q as the number located a distance q from p, in the positive or negative direction depending on whether q is positive or negative. Show that a number and its opposite have a sum of 0 (are additive inverses). Interpret sums of rational numbe'), ('1319', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.1c', '2', null, null, null, 'Understand subtraction of rational numbers as adding the additive inverse, p - q = p + (-q). Show that the distance between two rational numbers on the number line is the absolute value of their difference, and apply this principle in real-world contexts.'), ('1320', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.1d', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply properties of operations as strategies to add and subtract rational numbers.'), ('1321', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.2', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply and extend previous understandings of multiplication and division and of fractions to multiply and divide rational numbers.'), ('1322', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.2a', '2', null, null, null, 'Understand that multiplication is extended from fractions to rational numbers by requiring that operations continue to satisfy the properties of operations, particularly the distributive property, leading to products such as (-1)(-1) = 1 and the rules for'), ('1323', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.2b', '2', null, null, null, 'Understand that integers can be divided, provided that the divisor is not zero, and every quotient of integers (with non-zero divisor) is a rational number. If p and q are integers, then -(p/q) = (-p)/q = p/(-q). Interpret quotients of rational numbers by'), ('1324', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.2c', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply properties of operations as strategies to multiply and divide rational numbers.'), ('1325', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.2d', '2', null, null, null, 'Convert a rational number to a decimal using long division; know that the decimal form of a rational number terminates in 0s or eventually repeats.'), ('1326', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.3', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve real-world and mathematical problems involving the four operations with rational numbers.'), ('1327', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A', '2', null, null, null, 'Analyze proportional relationships and use them to solve real-world and mathematical problems.'), ('1328', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A.1', '2', null, null, null, 'Compute unit rates associated with ratios of fractions, including ratios of lengths, areas and other quantities measured in like or different units.'), ('1329', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A.2', '2', null, null, null, 'Recognize and represent proportional relationships between quantities.'), ('1330', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A.2a', '2', null, null, null, 'Decide whether two quantities are in a proportional relationship, e.g., by testing for equivalent ratios in a table or graphing on a coordinate plane and observing whether the graph is a straight line through the origin.'), ('1331', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A.2b', '2', null, null, null, 'Identify the constant of proportionality (unit rate) in tables, graphs, equations, diagrams, and verbal descriptions of proportional relationships.'), ('1332', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A.2c', '2', null, null, null, 'Represent proportional relationships by equations.'), ('1333', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A.2d', '2', null, null, null, 'Explain what a point (x, y) on the graph of a proportional relationship means in terms of the situation, with special attention to the points (0, 0) and (1, r) where r is the unit rate.'), ('1334', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.RP.A.3', '2', null, null, null, 'Use proportional relationships to solve multistep ratio and percent problems.'), ('1335', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.SP.A', '2', null, null, null, 'Use random sampling to draw inferences about a population.'), ('1336', 'CCSS.Math.Content.7.SP.A.1', '2', null, null, null, 'Understand that statistics can be used to gain information