g pairs of sides and corresponding pairs of angles are congruent.'), ('1513', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-CO.B.8', '2', null, null, null, 'Explain how the criteria for triangle congruence (ASA, SAS, and SSS) follow from the definition of congruence in terms of rigid motions.'), ('1514', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-CO.C', '2', null, null, null, 'Prove geometric theorems'), ('1515', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-CO.C.10', '2', null, null, null, 'Prove theorems about triangles.'), ('1516', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-CO.C.11', '2', null, null, null, 'Prove theorems about parallelograms.'), ('1517', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-CO.C.9', '2', null, null, null, 'Prove theorems about lines and angles.'), ('1518', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-CO.D', '2', null, null, null, 'Make geometric constructions'), ('1519', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-CO.D.12', '2', null, null, null, 'Make formal geometric constructions with a variety of tools and methods (compass and straightedge, string, reflective devices, paper folding, dynamic geometric software, etc.). Copying a segment; copying an angle; bisecting a segment; bisecting an angle; '), ('1520', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-CO.D.13', '2', null, null, null, 'Construct an equilateral triangle, a square, and a regular hexagon inscribed in a circle.'), ('1521', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-GMD.A', '2', null, null, null, 'Explain volume formulas and use them to solve problems'), ('1522', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-GMD.A.1', '2', null, null, null, 'Give an informal argument for the formulas for the circumference of a circle, area of a circle, volume of a cylinder, pyramid, and cone.'), ('1523', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-GMD.A.2', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Give an informal argument using Cavalieri\'s principle for the formulas for the volume of a sphere and other solid figures.'), ('1524', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-GMD.A.3', '2', null, null, null, 'Use volume formulas for cylinders, pyramids, cones, and spheres to solve problems.&lt;sup&gt;???&lt;/sup&gt;'), ('1525', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-GMD.B',