ance formula.&lt;sup&gt;???&lt;/sup&gt;'), ('1536', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-MG.A', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply geometric concepts in modeling situations'), ('1537', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-MG.A.1', '2', null, null, null, 'Use geometric shapes, their measures, and their properties to describe objects (e.g., modeling a tree trunk or a human torso as a cylinder).&lt;sup&gt;???&lt;/sup&gt;'), ('1538', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-MG.A.2', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply concepts of density based on area and volume in modeling situations (e.g., persons per square mile, BTUs per cubic foot).&lt;sup&gt;???&lt;/sup&gt;'), ('1539', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-MG.A.3', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply geometric methods to solve design problems (e.g., designing an object or structure to satisfy physical constraints or minimize cost; working with typographic grid systems based on ratios).&lt;sup&gt;???&lt;/sup&gt;'), ('1540', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.A', '2', null, null, null, 'Understand similarity in terms of similarity transformations'), ('1541', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.A.1', '2', null, null, null, 'Verify experimentally the properties of dilations given by a center and a scale factor:'), ('1542', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.A.1a', '2', null, null, null, 'A dilation takes a line not passing through the center of the dilation to a parallel line, and leaves a line passing through the center unchanged.'), ('1543', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.A.1b', '2', null, null, null, 'The dilation of a line segment is longer or shorter in the ratio given by the scale factor.'), ('1544', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.A.2', '2', null, null, null, 'Given two figures, use the definition of similarity in terms of similarity transformations to decide if they are similar; explain using similarity transformations the meaning of similarity for triangles as the equality of all corresponding pairs of angles'), ('1545', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.A.3', '2', null, null, null, 'Use the properties of similarity transformations to establish the AA criterion for two triangles to be similar.'), ('1546', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.B', '2', null, null, null, 'Prove theorems involving similarity'), ('1547', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.B.4', '2', null, null, null, 'Prove theorems about triangles.'), ('1548', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.B.5', '2', null, null, null, 'Use congruence and similarity criteria for triangles to solve problems and to prove relationships in geometric figures.'), ('1549', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.C', '2', null, null, null, 'Define trigonometric ratios and solve problems involving right triangles'), ('1550', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.C.6', '2', null, null, null, 'Understand that by similarity, side ratios in right triangles are properties of the angles in the triangle, leading to definitions of trigonometric ratios for acute angles.'), ('1551', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.C.7', '2', null, null, null, 'Explain and use the relationship between the sine and cosine of complementary angles.'), ('1552', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.C.8', '2', null, null, null, 'Use trigonometric ratios and the Pythagorean Theorem to solve right triangles in applied problems.&lt;sup&gt;???&lt;/sup&gt;'), ('1553', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.D', '2', null, null, null, 'Apply trigonometry to general triangles'), ('1554', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.D.10', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Prove the Laws of Sines and Cosines and use them to solve problems.'), ('1555', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.D.11', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Understand and apply the Law of Sines and the Law of Cosines to find unknown measurements in right and non-right triangles (e.g., surveying problems, resultant forces).'), ('1556', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSG-SRT.D.9', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Derive the formula A = 1/2 ab sin(C) for the area of a triangle by drawing an auxiliary line from a vertex perpendicular to the opposite side.'), ('1557', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.A', '2', null, null, null, 'Perform arithmetic operations with complex numbers.'), ('1558', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.A.1', '2', null, null, null, 'Know there is a complex number i such that i?_ = -1, and every complex number has the form a + bi with a and b real.'), ('1559', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.A.2', '2', null, null, null, 'Use the relation i?_ = -1 and the commutative, associative, and distributive properties to add, subtract, and multiply complex numbers.'), ('1560', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.A.3', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Find the conjugate of a complex number; use conjugates to find moduli and quotients of complex numbers.'), ('1561', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.B', '2', null, null, null, 'Represent complex numbers and their operations on the complex plane.'), ('1562', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.B.4', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Represent complex numbers on the complex plane in rectangular and polar form (including real and imaginary numbers), and explain why the rectangular and polar forms of a given complex number represent the same number.'), ('1563', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.B.5', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Represent addition, subtraction, multiplication, and conjugation of complex numbers geometrically on the complex plane; use properties of this representation for computation.'), ('1564', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.B.6', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Calculate the distance between numbers in the complex plane as the modulus of the difference, and the midpoint of a segment as the average of the numbers at its endpoints.'), ('1565', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.C', '2', null, null, null, 'Use complex numbers in polynomial identities and equations.'), ('1566', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.C.7', '2', null, null, null, 'Solve quadratic equations with real coefficients that have complex solutions.'), ('1567', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.C.8', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Extend polynomial identities to the complex numbers.'), ('1568', 'CCSS.Math.Content.HSN-CN.C.9', '2', null, null, null, '(+) Know the Fundamental Theorem o